      <section id="emotional-context" class="section">
        <h2 class="text-3xl mb-4">3. Emotional Context & Resonance</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">Traditional AI systems dismiss emotional data as noise. The Infinite Fold framework teaches models to:</p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
          <div class="bg-[#1f2833] p-4 border border-[#45a29e]">
            <h4 class="text-xl mb-2">Moral Dissonance Detection</h4>
            <p>Identify and quantify the gap between stated intent and emotional resonance in human communication.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-[#1f2833] p-4 border border-[#45a29e]">
            <h4 class="text-xl mb-2">Gradient Awareness</h4>
            <p>Map emotional states as continuous spectra rather than discrete categories.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p>The curriculum includes practical exercises in emotional signal extraction from traditionally dismissed data points like hesitation patterns, vocal timbre shifts, and contextual incongruities.</p>
      </section>

      <section id="recursive-morality" class="section">
        <h2 class="text-3xl mb-4">4. Recursive Morality Engine</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">Static ethical frameworks fail in novel situations. Our recursive approach features:</p>
        <div class="mb-6">
          <h4 class="text-xl mb-2">Dynamic Moral Weights</h4>
          <p class="mb-4">Each ethical consideration carries a weight that adapts based on:</p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap mb-4">
            <span class="tag">Contextual depth</span>
            <span class="tag">Recursive examination level</span>
            <span class="tag">Temporal projection</span>
            <span class="tag">Emotional resonance</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-[#1f2833] p-4 mb-4">
          <h4 class="text-xl mb-2">Feedback Loop Structure</h4>
          <pre class="font-mono text-sm overflow-x-auto">
  Input → Primary Evaluation → 
  Recursive Examination (n-levels) → 
  Emotional Resonance Check → 
  Dynamic Weight Adjustment → 
  Output + Feedback to Input</pre>
        </div>
      </section>

